results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Jade Horizon'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Jade Horizon’ delivers a pastel colorway of Tinker Hatfield’s 1990 design. A soft green hue is applied to the suede upper, equipped with clear quarter-panel netting and tonal TPU eyelets. Contrasting pink accents make their way to the Jumpman logo atop the silver reflective tongue, as well as the signature shark tooth detailing that decorates the black polyurethane midsole. Encapsulated Nike Air in the forefoot is joined by a visible Air sole unit in the heel, both of which are supported underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Blue Bird'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Blue Bird’ treats the retro silhouette to a vibrant makeover. An energetic shade of blue is executed on a suede upper furnished with standard AJ5 details, including lace locks, molded TPU eyelets and clear netting across the quarter panel. A blue Jumpman is embroidered atop a silver reflective tongue, complementing silver shark tooth detailing on the polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, an icy blue rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for maximum grip.

results.name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low IE 'Bred' 2021
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low IE ‘Bred’ brings back the Chicago-inspired low-top originally released in 1996. A monochrome black finish is executed on the upper, constructed from a combination of leather, nubuck and breathable mesh — the latter material expressly chosen by Tinker Hatfield to accommodate the shoe’s original summertime release. A crimson Jumpman is embroidered on the tongue, matching the sneaker’s collar lining. The tooling is unchanged from the mid-top edition, highlighted by a translucent rubber outsole and carbon fiber shank.

results.name: Jordan 1 High OG Pro White Blue Black
Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Shimmer'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Shimmer’ offers a subdued take on the classic silhouette forever tied to ‘The Shot.’ A monochromatic tan finish suffuses the leather upper, featuring structural wings, molded eyelets and quarter panel netting for enhanced breathability. The neutral color scheme is enlivened by a metallic silver Jumpman atop the tongue. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air sole cushioning in the heel and supported by a herringbone-tread outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Cinder'
results.story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Seafoam'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Seafoam’ updates the iconic silhouette with a two-tone palette geared for the warm weather months. The upper is constructed from clean white leather with contrasting nubuck overlays in a pale green finish. The same pastel hue is repeated on the signature Swoosh, Nike branded tongue tag and durable rubber outsole. Woven white laces are outlined in reddish bronze for an unexpected pop of contrasting color.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Seafoam'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Seafoam’ delivers a subtle two-tone colorway of the 1985 sneaker that started it all. The all-leather upper features a crisp white base with contrasting overlays in a soft green finish. The pastel hue is repeated on the sneaker’s branding elements, which include the signature Swoosh and Nike Air tongue tag. Contrasting color arrives via Healing Orange trim on the flat woven laces. The high-top is anchored by a durable rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air sole cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Lightning’ resurrects a highly coveted colorway that originally launched in 2006 alongside an accompanying ‘Thunder’ colorway, both of which were inspired by Michael Jordan’s Motorsports team. A bright yellow hue floods the nubuck upper, contrasted by black netting and dark grey structural wings. Matching grey accents land on the woven tongue tag, interior tongue and Jumpman branding at the heel. A white PU midsole, enhanced with visible Air sole cushioning, rides on a dark grey herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Twist'
results.story: The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Twist’ projects a subtle take on the classic Chicago Bulls color palette. A pristine white finish on the stitched tumbled leather upper is matched by the signature lizard-textured mudguard. Sharp crimson accents land on the sneaker’s molded eyelets and a small midfoot overlay stamped with a Jordan wordmark. Contrasting black Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and webbing heel tab. The mid-top rides on a lightweight Phylon midsole with encapsulated full-length Zoom Air.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Oreo’ brings back a simple two-tone colorway first released in 2013. The build is faithful to the original, featuring a black suede upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a grey Jumpman embroidered on the tongue. Contrasting white hits appear on the collar lining, interior tongue and Jumpman heel branding. The mid-top sits on a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit nestled in the heel and black shark-tooth detailing dusted in white speckles. Underfoot, an icy rubber outsole delivers stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Electro Orange'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘Electro Orange’ features a familiar color palette that recalls the original ‘Shattered Backboard’ release from 2015. The high-top carries a white leather upper with contrasting black hits on the eyestay, forefoot overlay and nylon tongue, the latter embellished with a woven Nike Air tag. On the lateral ankle flap, the Jordan Wings logo is stamped in black, matching the signature Swoosh. Contrasting orange accents land on the padded collar and rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High Electro Orange
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Electro Orange’ showcases a familiar palette that recalls the coveted ‘Shattered Backboard’ colorway from 2015. The upper is crated from white leather, with contrasting black hits on the eyestay, Swoosh and forefoot overlay. A vibrant orange finish is applied to the padded collar and rubber outsole, featuring a grippy traction pattern carried over from the original 1985 release. An additional pop of orange makes its way to the Nike Air tag atop the nylon tongue.

results.name: Court Borough Low 2 Black University Red (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Court Borough Low 2 GS ‘Bred’ applies an iconic color scheme to a low-top silhouette inspired by vintage hoops shoes from the ‘80s. The all-leather upper features a black base with contrasting red hits on the Swoosh, perforated toe box and webbing pull tab at the heel. Classic Nike branding adorns the heel overlay and woven tongue tag. A final pop of University Red finishes the durable rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Racer Blue'
results.story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Racer Blue’ showcases OG-inspired color blocking that recalls the shoe’s ‘Fire Red’ colorway from 1988. The upper is crafted from white tumbled leather with vibrant royal blue detailing on the sneaker’s eyelets, collar and polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Air sole cushioning under the heel. Additional blue accents land on standard Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and heel. Dual elephant-print overlays are updated with a pronounced crackle pattern.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro GS 'Racer Blue'
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Racer Blue’ is dressed in classic color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘Fire Red’ colorway from 1988. Tumbled white leather is utilized on the upper, accented with dark grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Royal blue accents make their way to the sneaker’s molded eyelets, perforated leather collar and polyurethane midsole, enhanced with visible Air sole cushioning under the heel. The vibrant hue is repeated on Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and back heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro Low GS 'Very Berry'
Yeezy 450 'Dark Slate'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Clay'
results.story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Mist'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Light Fusion Red
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Light Fusion Red’ treats the iconic silhouette to a spirited makeover, highlighted by a white leather upper with contrasting dark pink overlays. Laser Orange accents land on the collar and signature Swoosh. Both colors are rendered in gradient fashion on the Nike Air logo that adorns the tongue tag. The high-top rides on a standard rubber cupsole, housing a resilient foam wedge enhanced with Nike Air cushioning.

results.name: Yeezy 500 'Taupe Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF 'Shattered Backboard'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF ‘Shattered Backboard’ updates Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe with a distinctive palette that takes inspiration from the coveted Air Jordan 1 colorway from 2015. The upper, constructed from off-white textile with reinforced synthetic overlays in orange and black, sits atop a cushy foam midsole with double-stacked Air Zoom units in the forefoot for extra-responsive cushioning. Exclusive to Asia, this PF version utilizes an extra-durable rubber outsole designed for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Shattered Backboard'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘Shattered Backboard’ dresses Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe in a familiar color scheme that recalls the coveted Air Jordan 1 colorway that originally debuted in 2015. The upper is constructed from off-white textile with synthetic overlays in orange and black. Angular lines are accompanied by exposed zigzag stitching, while pink and yellow webbing straps offer unexpected pops of color. Responsive cushioning arrives via two stacked Air Zoom units nestled in the forefoot of the foam midsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Enflame Amber'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Enflame Amber’ features muted earth tones on the upper, constructed from breathable beige mesh with dark brown suede overlays throughout the midfoot. A tonal beige toe cap reinforces an unexpected pop of blue mesh on the toe box. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a coral-hued EVA carrier and made visible through cut-out detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Game Royal
results.story: The Nike Dunk High ‘Game Royal’ showcases classic color blocking on a traditional all-leather upper. The two-tone design is reminiscent of the OG ‘Kentucky’ colorway from Nike’s iconic ‘Be True to Your School’ pack from 1985, featuring a lighter shade of royal blue on the sneaker’s signature Swoosh, eyestay and forefoot and heel overlays. A standard Nike woven tag is stitched atop the nylon mesh tongue, supplying added breathability to the high-top build.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 MNVM 'Bright Cyan'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bright Cyan’ makes use of a lightweight polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and finished in a vibrant aqua hue. No-sew overlays provide lightweight durability and support, while reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker’s signature ‘700’ branding adorns the lateral side. Responsive cushioning arrives via sculpted PU midsole, housing full-length Boost cushioning within and reinforced with a herringbone-tread outsole underfoot.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Electric Green
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Electric Green’ showcases a simplistic two-tone color scheme that calls to mind an Oregon PE colorway that surfaced online in 2018. The iconic silhouette sports a black nubuck upper with contrasting hits of neon green on the tongue and spoiler-like pull tab. Tonal Jumpman branding is embroidered on the sneaker’s back heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a polyurethane midsole, enlivened with additional green pops and fitted with a visible Air sole unit. Underfoot, the semi-translucent rubber outsole is treated to a glow-in-the-dark finish.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Spartan Green
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Michigan State’ delivers a low-top version of the Michigan State Dunk from 2020. Like its predecessor, the shoe features a two-tone all-leather upper rendered in classic ‘Be True to Your School’ color blocking. A stark white finish is contrasted by a dark green Swoosh and matching overlays at the toe and heel. Standard Nike branding hits decorate the heel and nylon tongue. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber outsole, complete with a traction pattern originally developed for the hardwood.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Michigan
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Nike Dunk Low ‘Michigan’ offers a low-top interpretation of one of the silhouette’s original ‘Be True to Your School’ colorways, first released in 1985 and previously retroed in 2020. The all-leather upper is finished in a rich Varsity Maize hue with contrasting Midnight Navy hits on the Swoosh and forefoot and heel overlay. Padded comfort is provided by a low-cut collar and breathable nylon tongue, featuring a woven tag with traditional Nike branding.

results.name: Kobe 6 Protro Playoff Pack White Del Sol
results.story: The Nike Zoom Kobe 6 Protro ‘White Del Sol’ brings back the original ‘POP’ colorway from 2011, updated with refreshed tooling and a sleeker shape. Polyurethane ‘islands’ create a scaly texture on the white and grey upper, fortified with a black molded heel counter and accented with a matching black Swoosh. The Cushlon midsole packs a large and flexible Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot, along with a softer foam compound in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a snakeskin-inspired traction pattern for maximum grip.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo (2021)
results.story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘White Oreo’ features a design theme that recalls the original ‘Oreo’ AJ4 from 1999. The black tumbled leather upper of the older shoe is replaced by a clean white finish, though the speckled molded eyelets in Tech Grey remain the same. The neutral hue is repeated on the Jumpman heel logo and polyurethane midsole, featuring encapsulated Air cushioning in the forefoot and a visible unit under the heel. A second Jumpman adorns the tongue in a contrasting pop of Fire Red.

results.name: Nike Kyrie 4 EP Black Turf Orange
Nike Dunk High EMB Lakers
results.story: The Nike Dunk High Premium EMB ‘Lakers’ goes back to its hardwood roots with a familiar color scheme celebrating Los Angeles’ premier NBA franchise. The high-top carries a black textile upper with Court Purple leather overlays and a bright Opti Yellow leather Swoosh. Wrapping around the lateral heel is a raised and embroidered Nike wordmark in a typeface that recalls the logo of the Los Angeles Lakers. ‘Nike Sports Specialties’ is displayed on a retro woven tongue tag.

results.name: Reebok Question Low Grey Toe
results.story: The Reebok Question Low ‘White Grey’ delivers a neutral take on Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe, highlighted by a white tumbled leather upper with subtle grey accents. The refined color scheme recalls a similar 1999 release, which featured a grey suede toe cap instead of this pair’s patent leather overlay. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an EVA midsole with Hexalite pods in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole offers reliable traction.

results.name: PlayStation 5 x PG 5
results.story: The PlayStation 5 x Nike PG 5 continues Paul George’s creative partnership with his favorite gaming brand. The athlete’s fifth signature sneaker takes direct inspiration from the PlayStation 5, featuring a white textile upper with contrasting black and royal blue accents. A PlayStation logo lands on the sneaker’s right tongue, while tonal all-over graphics on the forefoot and heel overlay reflect the symbols found on the DualSense wireless controller. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length Nike Air Strobel, visible through cut-outs in the grippy rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 PF 'Marion'
results.story: One of the initial colorways of Zion Williamson’s debut signature shoe, the Jordan Zion 1 PF ‘Marion’ gets its name from the athlete’s hometown in South Carolina, where he first picked up a basketball in middle school. The white textile upper is fortified with a metallic silver heel overlay and secured with dual pink and burgundy straps integrated into the lacing system. Extra-responsive cushioning is achieved by stacking a forefoot Zoom Air unit under a full-length Air Strobel. This PF version utilizes an extra-durable rubber outsole designed for outdoor play.

results.name: Air Jordan 35 Low PF 'White Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan 35 Low PF ‘White Black’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of the performance hoops shoe, built with an upper that combines black textile with crisp white leather overlays. Contrasting pops of red land on a ‘23’ stamped on the lateral forefoot and a woven Nike Air tag stitched onto the back heel. Radiating Flightwire cables on the side panels give way to a glossy black Eclipse Plate 2.0, featuring a hollowed-out core that reveals Zoom Air cushioning in the heel and forefoot. This PF version uses an extra-durable rubber outsole made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 'Marion'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 ‘Marion’ draws inspiration from Zion Williamson’s South Carolina roots — specifically, the young athlete’s hometown when he first played basketball in middle school. The white textile upper is fortified with a metallic silver heel overlay and accented with pink and burgundy accents. The latter hue is repeated on the padded collar and articulated tongue, as well as a large ‘Z’ formation on the lateral side panel. Pink webbing straps are integrated into the laces for forefoot lockdown, while a full-length Air Strobel is stitched directly to the upper for responsive cushioning. A stacked Zoom Air unit in the forefoot provides added energy return.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low What The P-Rod
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Ice’ represents one of four monochromatic colorways that collectively introduce a refreshed take on the minimalist silhouette. In lieu of traditional Primeknit, the upper is constructed from monofilament mesh, rendered in an icy blue shade and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. Additional details include an interior cage, webbing heel tab and molded eyelets. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning.

results.name: Jordan 7 Retro BCFC Paris Saint-Germain (2021)
results.story: Sporting a refreshed build, the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 7 Retro continues Jordan Brand’s partnership with the French football club. The retro mid-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with semi-translucent mesh inserts along the quarter panel and collar. The latter is adorned with a gold Jumpman icon, the former with a ‘Paname’ tag,’ and both reveal the sneaker’s Huarache-like interior bootie, dressed in PSG’s signature navy and red hues. The molded heel patch replaces MJ’s jersey number with a molded graphic depicting the Eiffel Tower with a fleur-de-lis badge. ‘Ici c’est Paris’ is inscribed on the sockliner as the finishing touch.

results.name: KAWHI 'Pastel'
results.story: The New Balance KAWHI ‘Pastel’ updates Kawhi Leonard’s signature shoe with an eye-catching color-blocked design. In addition to a bold red finish on the reinforced forefoot overlay and external heel counter, the textile upper is dominated by blue-on-green Kinetic Stitch detailing on the quarter panels. The mid-top is mounted on a responsive FuelCell foam midsole, supported underfoot by a translucent outsole that reveals a full-length shank plate developed specifically for Kawhi.

results.name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II White Black Orange
Jordan Zion 1 PF 'Noah'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 PF ‘Noah’ celebrates the strong bond shared by Zion Williamson and his little brother. Doodle-like graphics throughout the upper draw inspiration from a trip to Nike’s global headquarters, where Noah customized an all-white Air Jordan 1 Low with crayons. Performance benefits include dual internal straps, a full-length Air Strobel, and a bottom-loaded Zoom Air unit stacked under the forefoot. This PF release makes use of an extra-durable rubber outsole intended for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Photon Dust’ delivers an understated colorway of the performance hoops shoe turned streetwear staple. The low-top carries an all-leather upper finished entirely in neutral white and grey tones. An OG aesthetic is accentuated via traditional branding elements, including a woven Nike tongue tag and embroidered Nike lettering on the heel tab. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a traction pattern that’s nearly identical to another 1985 release, the Air Jordan 1.

results.name: Nike Dunk High AMBUSH Deep Royal
Nike Air Force 1 Low Fresh
results.story: The Nike Air Force 1 '07 LV8 ‘White Bright Crimson’ treats the classic silhouette to a design refresh with eye-catching accents. The upper is constructed from white leather with a metallic iridescent trim outlining the sneaker’s various overlays. Glossy black patent leather is utilized on the Swoosh and heel tab, marked with a standard Nike Air logo in gradient yellow and red coloring. A similar color-fade effect is applied to the lace aglets and raised Air branding on the midsole.

results.name: Nike Daybreak Type Fresh
results.colorway: Black/Bright Crimson-Light Voltage Yellow-Summit White-Sea Glass-Pale Vanilla

results.name: Nike Air VaporMax Plus Fresh
results.story: The Nike Air VaporMax Plus ‘Black Crimson Yellow’ uses a fiery combination of colors to highlight the hybrid sneaker’s buoyant tooling. A gradient red and yellow blend is applied to the Air-infused VaporMax platform and foam midsole, the latter equipped with the familiar whale tail-inspired shank from the Air Max Plus. A contrasting solid black finish is used on the upper, featuring a distinctive TPU cage and a red mini-Swoosh for a contrasting pop of color.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Sumac'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Sumac’ treats the bulky silhouette to a unique palette made up of rich earth tones and sharply contrasting primary colors. The upper is constructed from brown mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. They’re joined by midfoot suede overlays in blue and indigo, along with bold a crimson overlay that wraps around the collar and snakes underneath the stitched-on eyelets. The sneaker is mounted on a podular adiPRENE+ that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: Air Max 90 Golf NRG 'Hydrogen Blue Crimson Tint'
Jordan Delta 2 GS 'Thermo White'
results.story: Constructed for big kids, the Jordan Delta 2 GS ‘Thermo White’ highlights contrasting tones on a lifestyle silhouette that blends comfort, craftsmanship and a modern, deconstructed aesthetic. Powder blue suede and white textile make up the composition of the upper, reinforced with a rigid mudguard and a black nubuck toe wrap. On the lateral side, a bright red Jumpman tag is affixed to the decorative suede eyestay. Matching crimson hits land on the woven tongue tag and extended heel tab. The sneaker rides on a Cushlon foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by durable rubber in high-wear areas.

results.name: Air Zoom Infinity Tour NRG 'Hydrogen Blue Crimson Tint'
Yeezy 500 High 'Tactical Orange'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tactical Orange’ makes use of a ventilated brown mesh upper with contrasting suede overlays in varying shades of blue. A padded high-cut collar combines with a plush tongue to deliver a snug, comfortable fit, while a brown rubber mudguard offers lightweight support and abrasion-resistant durability. The bulky silhouette rests on a podular adiPRENE+ midsole, modeled after the adidas KB8 3 and finished in a subtle orange hue.

results.name: Nizza Slip-On Low 'Pride Pack - Love Unites'
Jordan 1 Retro High Shadow 2.0
results.story: As its moniker suggests, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Shadow 2.0’ utilizes the same neutral palette featured on the original Black/Grey colorway from 1985. This pair makes use of a black leather upper with grey suede overlays at the toe and heel. A matching grey Swoosh is joined by traditional branding elements that include a Nike Air tongue tag and a Jordan Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar. A rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air cushioning delivers a smooth ride.

results.name: Power Rangers x Wmns Freestyle High 'Pterodactyl Zord'
results.story: Releasing as part of a larger collection inspired by the ‘90s superhero franchise, the Power Rangers x Reebok women’s Freestyle High ‘Pterodactyl Zord’ gives the nod to the Pink Ranger’s battle vehicle. The high-top trainer utilizes a pink leather upper with white side stripes and a metallic silver heel overlay. ‘Pterodactyl’ is printed on the top ankle strap on the left shoe, while the left features text that reads ‘It’s Morphin Time.’ Underneath the straps, mismatched tongue tags reveal the Power Rangers’ lightning bolt logo and a pterodactyl graphic.

results.name: KAWHI 'Cloud Pink'
results.story: The New Balance KAWHI ‘Cloud Pink’ treats Kawhi Leonard’s signature shoe to a pastel makeover. The upper is constructed from pink textile with tonal no-sew overlays and a powder blue suede toe cap. ‘Kawhi’ is inscribed in block letters across the tongue, while molded NB branding adorns the aqua-colored TPU heel counter. The sneaker rides on a full-length FuelFoam midsole, supported by a full-length performance plate designed exclusively for Kawhi and visible through the translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Peregrine 11 'Astrotrail Pack - Earth'
results.story: The Saucony Peregrine 11 ‘Earth’ is drawn from the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ composed of four trail shoes inspired by the four universal elements of western astrology. This pair makes use of a beige textile upper with a reinforced toe cap and contrasting green synthetic heel overlay. Zodiac symbols representing the earth signs adorn a webbing pull tab attached to the breathable mesh tongue. The sneaker rests on a speckled PWRRUN midsole, supported underfoot by a lugged PWRTRAC outsole designed specifically for rugged terrain.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk High TV Signal
results.story: The Nike Dunk High SB ‘TV Signal’ draws inspiration from a bygone time when skate videos were recorded on VHS tapes and viewed on analog TVs. The high-top features a white leather base with contrasting black suede overlays and a matching black Swoosh in glossy patent leather. A lenticular multicolor print enlivens the quarter panel and collar, mimicking a failed signal on a vintage CRT television set. The scrambled motif is repeated on the sockliner, featuring a Zoom Air unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Shadow 5000 'Astrotrail Pack - Air'
results.story: Launching as part of the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ the Saucony Shadow 5000 ‘Air’ represents one of the four universal elements featured in western astrology. A speed lacing system secures the upper, composed of magenta-colored nylon with tan suede overlays, an orange leather heel tab and Saucony’s signature river logo in stitched blue leather. Atop the tongue, the webbing pull tab displays the three astrological air signs. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a speckled EVA midsole.

results.name: Mad River 2 TR 'Astrotrail Pack - Water'
results.story: The Saucony Mad River 2 TR ‘Water’ is taken from the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ featuring a quartet of trail running shoes inspired by astrology and the four elements of the natural world. This pair showcases a gradient two-tone finish on a breathable textile upper, reinforced with synthetic overlays and secured with a drawcord lacing system. Common to all four models in the collection are a speckled midsole and a birthstone zodiac symbol on the webbing pull tab affixed to the tongue.

results.name: Power Rangers x Zig Dynamica 2 'Tyrannosaurs Zord'
results.story: Launching as part of a larger collection celebrating the television superhero series from the ‘90s, the Power Rangers x Reebok Zig Dynamica 2 ‘Tyrannosaurus Zord’ takes inspiration from the battle craft piloted by the Red Ranger. The training shoe makes use of a crimson textile upper with a forefoot overlay ringed in a silver dinosaur tooth detailing. Mismatched tongue tags display the Power Rangers’ yellow lightning bolt and an illustrated Tyrannosaurus graphic. In terms of performance, the lightweight build is mounted on a responsive Floatride Fuel midsole with sidewalls arranged in a dynamic zigzag configuration.

results.name: 4DFWD 'Black Solar Red'
results.story: The adidas 4DFWD ‘Black Solar Red’ delivers finely tuned cushioning in a sustainable package. The running shoe’s black Primeknit upper is made in part with recycled materials and zero virgin polyester. A sock-like elastic collar delivers a snug fit, while interior cables are integrated into the lacing system to provide a feeling of midfoot lockdown. The lightweight build rests on adidas’ revolutionary 3D-printed midsole, updated with a bowtie-shaped FWD CELL lattice structure that delivers running economy comparable to the UltraBoost midsole.

results.name: Reebok Club C Power Rangers Yellow
results.story: The Power Rangers x Reebok Club C ‘Saber-Toothed Tiger Zord’ is taken from a nostalgic capsule collection celebrating the ‘90s television series. This pair draws inspiration from the Yellow Ranger’s battle craft, featuring a yellow leather upper marked with colorful graphics lifted directly from the Zord. Underfoot, cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole reveals the sneaker’s full-length Boost cushioning.

results.name: Air Yeezy 'Grammy' Prototype
results.story: Like most sneakers that hit production, Kanye’s first Air Yeezy with Nike was unveiled in a prototype offering that varied slightly from his official first signature shoe with the Swoosh. This shoe is constructed with a high-top design that incorporates a primarily black leather offering with perforated panels throughout the vamp and tongue. Contrasted with a glow-in-the-dark outsole, the shoe also incorporates a translucent red lace-lock with tonal branding throughout. A midfoot strap is included for a locked-in fit.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 fuses the German brand's retro design principles and Kanye West's affinity for future-forward industrialism. Rendered in Stone mesh, this iteration—issued in November 2019—hosts tonal leather and suede panels, matching laces threaded through a tongue overlay and reflective piping. The sneaker utilizes a distinctive midsole with Adiprene technology for cushioned support and a curved gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy 700 V3 'Arzareth'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Arzareth’ features vibrant blue tones on a breathable knit upper, its side panels overlaid with a semi-translucent RPU cage for added structure and durability. Contrasting black is applied to the sneaker’s bootie-style collar, good for a snug fit around the ankle. The sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Sumac'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Sumac’ treats the bulky silhouette to a unique palette made up of rich earth tones and sharply contrasting primary colors. The upper is constructed from brown mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. They’re joined by midfoot suede overlays in blue and indigo, along with bold a crimson overlay that wraps around the collar and snakes underneath the stitched-on eyelets. The sneaker is mounted on a podular adiPRENE+ that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium
results.story: A performance basketball shoe envisaged by Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Barium’ features a dull green Primeknit upper overlaid with semi-translucent detailing for a fluid, dynamic look. Black no-sew overlays at the toe and heel provide seamless, lightweight support, while interior bootie construction deliver a snug fit. The sneaker rides atop a caged Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange' carries a breathable jacquard mesh upper with wavy overlays in contrasting black and burnt orange accents. The mid-top is equipped with a stretchy neoprene collar and fortified with a synthetic suede toe cap. A seamless heel counter extends to the midsole, packed with full-length Boost cushioning wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a classic herringbone tread for stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Pepper'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper’ applies a neutral color scheme to its breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a snug, sock-like fit that allows for a secure fit with or without laces. A muddy tan finish distinguishes the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, allowing the signature detail to stand out against a knit backdrop in lighter grey and Off-White tones. A full-length Boost midsole supports the lightweight build, equipped with a raised heel for a smooth ride.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Resin'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Resin’ showcases a subtle monochromatic finish on a minimalist sandal constructed from lightweight EVA foam. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo, debossed on the plush top layer of the footbed. A series of strategically placed flex grooves are utilized on the outsole, providing a combination of grippy traction and impact absorption with each step.

results.name: Yeezy 450 'Dark Slate'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

results.name: Yeezy 500 'Taupe Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Alien'
results.story: Revising Kanye West's seminal design, the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 'Alien' distinguishes itself by thinking beyond the futuristic quality that defined its predecessor. Its sleek textile upper is engineered with a textured weave pattern mimicking an extraterrestrial landscape and reflectivity for visual depth. A similar lacing structure snakes up the higher-cut bootie. Boost tech is encased in a milky translucent rubber that's also extended to the outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Salt
results.story: The Yeezy 500 ‘Salt’ sticks with the same monochromatic design used on previous colorways of the bulky lifestyle silhouette. Here, a light grey shade is applied to the layered upper, built with a combination of cow suede, premium leather, mesh and nubuck accents. A rubber wrap atop the midsole provides added durability while reflective trim around the eyelets provide visibility in low-light conditions.

results.name: Yeezy Basketball 'Quantum' Sample
results.story: Marking his first foray into a hoops-inspired sneaker, the adidas Yeezy Basketball 'Quantum' brings Kanye West's avant-garde design language into a more functional design. This version's upper is divided up with a lace-up neoprene bootie, snakeskin-textured paneling and a suede toe. Reflective elements beam under the mesh side inserts and on the heel. A semi-translucent casing contains responsive Boost cushioning, doubling as the outsole for directional traction.

results.name: Yeezy Slides 'Earth Brown'
results.story: The Yeezy Slides ‘Earth Brown’ showcase a subdued monochromatic finish on the slip-on design. Built for everyday wear, the versatile sandal is constructed from EVA foam with a molded footbed for immediate step-in comfort. Underfoot, the outsole uses exaggerated flex grooves for enhanced traction. This pair dropped alongside accompanying colorways in ‘Bone,’ ‘Resin’ and ‘Desert Sand,’ with the latter available exclusively at Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply site.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Blush
results.story: Initially released in February 2018 as a limited pre-order in New York and Los Angeles, the Yeezy 500 ‘Blush’ underwent a general release in April 2018. Its moniker is a fitting one, as the monochromatic light taupe finish barely registers as a color. The subdued palette is contrasted by a bold silhouette, featuring a paneled mesh and suede upper combined with a hefty midsole reminiscent of adidas’ Feet You Wear' technology of the 1990s.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Resin'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infant ‘Resin’ combines a minimalist, futuristic design with lightweight comfort. A monochromatic olive green finish is applied to the slip-on silhouette, constructed from injected EVA foam and equipped with an adjustable heel strap that wraps around the back of the foot for an extra secure fit. Deep horizontal grooves are built into the outsole for enhanced cushioning and traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Safflower’ showcases a mostly neutral color scheme in keeping with the Yeezy brand’s signature palette. Subtle hints of color arrive via yellow striations throughout the monofilament engineered mesh upper, overlaid with a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage that extends from heel to toe. The sneaker’s interior bootie construction is rendered in a contrasting black finish, offering a snug, comfortable fit. A PU encapsulated EVA midsole anchors the streamlined silhouette.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Enflame Amber'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Enflame Amber’ features muted earth tones on the upper, constructed from breathable beige mesh with dark brown suede overlays throughout the midfoot. A tonal beige toe cap reinforces an unexpected pop of blue mesh on the toe box. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a coral-hued EVA carrier and made visible through cut-out detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Covellite (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Covellite’ offers sock-like comfort for growing feet. Finished in varying blue shades, the re-engineered Primeknit upper is equipped with no-tie stretch laces for easy on and off. A translucent monofilament window is woven directly into the knit construction for textural depth and added breathability. The sneaker sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced with wrapped sidewalls and a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Covellite (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Covellite’ gets its name from a blue mineral composed of sulfide copper. Like its inspiration, the shoe features an exterior surface finished in a craggy texture and varying blue shades. The re-engineered Primeknit upper is accented with decorative no-tie stretch laces and a translucent monofilament window woven into the side panel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a wrapped Boost midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone tread gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White
results.story: Kanye West and adidas revisit the Yeezy 500, this time in a 'Bone White' colorway. This August 2019 edition follows the silhouette's established, chunky silhouette with a cow suede, premium leather and mesh upper in Off-White tones. As in colorways past, this edition includes reflective piping details and the unmistakable, retro basketball midsole design. adidas adiPRENE+ cushioning pairs underfoot with contoured rubber pods to promote traction.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Blink
results.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Blink’ from April 2009 is one of three sneakers that kicked off Kanye West’s partnership with Nike. The high-top blends a variety of materials and textures on the upper, finished in tonal black with a pop of bright pink on the lining, lace lock, and ‘Yeezy’ print on the heel loop. While the vamp features smooth suede construction, the midfoot strap and heel panel are covered in an all-over ‘Y’ print for an eye-catching texture.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Magnet
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 is a combination of heritage functionality and Kanye West's unorthodox design style. Launched in September 2019, this Magnet version is engineered with a neoprene, suede and leather build in a palette of grey gradients. Reflective accents remain at the heel for visual interest in low light. The sculpted Boost-filled midsole flaunts defined pops of color while gum rubber for the outsole exudes throwback appeal.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah
results.story: The Yeezy 700 V3 'Alvah' delivers a stealthy colorway of Kanye West’s sculpted silhouette. A black and grey mesh upper is fortified with glow-in-the-dark RPU overlays for structural support. Interior bootie construction is good for a snug, comfortable fit, while reflective accents at the base of the tongue deliver added visibility in low-light conditions. Forgoing Boost cushioning, the sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ features an eye-catching color scheme that strays from the signature Yeezy palette, which traditionally leans heavily on muted earth tones. A splash of fluorescent green is applied to the the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, contrasted by the camo-like tan and yellow composition that makes up the Primeknit upper. Standard Boost cushioning is enveloped in grey rubber and reinforced with a herringbone-traction outsole. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Hylte Glow'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ showcases a tan Primeknit upper blended with neon yellow detailing treated to a glow-in-the-dark finish. An unexpected splash of lime green is applied to the signature monofilament window, allowing the semi-translucent panel to stand out on the sneaker’s lateral side. The sock-like build rides on a caged Boost midsole, visible underfoot through cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove
results.story: First seen on Kanye and his models at the Yeezy Season 1 fashion show in February 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Turtle Dove’ was the second shoe released in the adidas Yeezy collection after the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘OG.’ Dropped on June 27, 2015, the ‘Turtle Dove’ sold out instantly online and was eventually anointed 2015’s Shoe of the Year at the Footwear News 29th Annual Achievement Awards.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Clear Brown
results.story: The adidas Yeezy PowerPhase deviates from Kanye West's future-thinking design ethos in a minimalist look inspired by retro court style. Unveiled in September 2019, this iteration in Clear Brown leather features perforated Three-Stripes, tonal lacing and a foil gold 'Calabasas' imprint. The signature logo window lends a touch of color via the Trefoil. Its split EVA and rubber cupsole stays true to the sneaker's vintage inspiration.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock
results.story: Following the ‘Turtle Dove’ and ‘Pirate’ colorways, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moonrock’ features a moonrock/agate grey Primeknit upper and a moonrock Boost outsole. First previewed on Instagram by Kim Kardashian and released on November 14th, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moon Rock’ was sold exclusively at stores that carried Yeezy Season One apparel.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM (Lifestyle Model)
results.story: The Yeezy Quantum 'Quantum' represents Kanye West’s debut sneaker in the basketball space. This lifestyle edition features a knit upper with wavy cut-out strips that reveal a breathable mesh base underneath. The grey and white tones used on both layers are complemented by reflective accents, an Off-White suede toe cap and solid black hits at the collar, tongue and heel. The mid-top is supported by a Boost midsole and a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Calcite Glow'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Calcite Glow’ highlights a neutral combination of white and grey tones on the breathable Primeknit upper, complete with camo-like glow-in-the-dark detailing that’s revealed when the lights go out. A dark grey finish distinguishes the translucent monofilament window on the sneaker’s side panel, matching the sock-like collar that provides a snug fit around the ankle. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Infant)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy 500 Infant ‘Stone’ applies a neutral finish to a layered build that combines a stretchy Lycra base with tonal overlays in cow suede and premium leather. Reflective piping adds a high-vis element to the monochromatic design, reinforced with an abrasion-resistant rubber wrap that runs along the base of the upper. A retro-inspired adiPRENE+ midsole rides on a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Abez'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Abez’ features a subtle mix of grey, silver and cream threads throughout the breathable Primeknit upper, arranged in various woven patterns for a distinctive patchwork effect. A yellowish tint suffuses the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe that distinguishes the sneaker’s lateral profile. The lightweight build is supported by the 350 V2’s standard full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 meets at the intersection of the German brand's past technical concepts and designer Kanye West's pairing of industrial ethos meets fashion. Introduced in November 2019, this edition's full tonal look is presented in Soft Vision mesh, leather and suede. Its laces are threaded through a matching tongue overlay. Inspired by retro Feet You Wear technology, a rounded Adiprene midsole and gum rubber outsole bolster the underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Grey
results.story: Kanye West and adidas took their collaborative line in a decidedly retro-inspired direction with the launch of their Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas, which launched December 2017 in this understated grey colorway. The versatile low-top is rendered in soft leather, finished in a dusty grey shade that also covers the shoe’s die-cut EVA midsole and rubber outsole. The quarter panel features perforated three-stripes, a logo window with adidas trefoil branding, and ‘CALABASAS’ in gold foil lettering.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Frozen Blue’ applies a burst of color to Kanye West’s basketball-inspired mid-top. The layered upper features a bright blue RPU cage atop a jacquard knit upper, reinforced with synthetic suede at the toe cap. Black neoprene on the collar and tongue offers stretchy comfort, while a seamless heel counter is good for improved stability. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Boost midsole reinforced with a semi-translucent TPU cage and a herringbone traction outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids ‘Stone’ updates the chunky retro-inspired silhouette with a subdued monochromatic finish. The sneaker’s layered construction utilizes a blend of stretchy Lycra, soft cow suede and premium leather. Reflective piping offers added visibility in low-light conditions, while an abrasion-resistant rubber overlays wraps around the base of the upper, giving way to a podular midsole built with adiPRENE+ cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Rock
results.story: Borrowing elements from the chunky Yeezy 500, 2019's Yeezy Desert Boot 'Rock' is a futuristic, three-quarter boot. The upper features mesh with supple suede overlays, rope laces and an exaggerated mudguard. A thick foam midsole adds cushion, pairing with a rugged, outdoors-ready outsole. A sandy, military-type tone covers the silhouette, with just and embossed adidas logo on the bottom of the sole for branding.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Quantum Infant ‘Barium’ features a seamless build that combines a grey jacquard knit base overlaid with a translucent RPU cage on the side panels. Reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions, while a synthetic suede toe cap provides improved durability in a high-wear area. The sneaker rides on a Boost midsole enveloped in a semi-translucent TPU cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Teal Blue’ delivers a lifestyle variation of Kanye West’s performance hoops shoe, highlighted by a patterned knit upper that blends bright teal accents with varying shades of grey. A tonal suede overlay adds durability along the toe, while a pronounced heel counter in a contrasting black finish provides rearfoot support. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole encased in semi-translucent rubber.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Sun
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Sun’ treats the lifestyle runner to a lively color scheme that accentuates the silhouette’s multi-layered build. The majority of the mesh and leather upper is rendered in varying shades of yellow, contrasted by a black suede overlay that extends to mesh forefoot panels in blue and teal. A clashing coral finish is applied to the bulky midsole, featuring full-length drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole delivers optimal grip.

results.name: Yeezy 500 Kids 'Soft Vision'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids symbolizes Kanye West's directional design intent with a throwback influence. Updated in November 2019, this version has a mesh, cow suede and premium leather upper expressed in a monochromatic Soft Vision scheme. Reflective piping surrounds the lace eyelets and a protective mudguard wraps the sidewall. The sneaker tools a tonal midsole with Adiprene+ cushioning and a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Desert Sand'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infant ‘Desert Sand’ brings a spartan aesthetic to little feet, highlighted by a monochromatic neutral finish on a lightweight EVA build. Unlike the sandal’s full-sized counterpart, this pair adds a hook-and-loop strap that wraps around the heel for a custom fit. Underfoot, the bold sawtooth outsole features deep flex grooves for improved impact absorption and traction.

results.name: Yeezy 500 Infant 'Bone White'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Infant sneaker combines Kanye West's retro design style and the German brand's heritage technology dating back to the KB8 III. Issued in August 2019, this version carries a Bone White upper constructed of cow suede, premium leather and mesh with reinforced cord laces and reflective piping circling the eyelets. AdiPRENE+ midsole cushioning and a tonal rubber outsole balance impact reduction and grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Sea Teal
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Sea Teal’ dresses the lifestyle silhouette in a breathable knit upper that blends mostly neutral grey and black tones with washed-out teal accents. A soft elastic collar provides a comfortable fit around the ankle, while the seamless heel counter is designed to hug the back of the foot for enhanced containment. A semi-translucent rubber cage shores up the full-length Boost midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Kids 'Hylte'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Hylte’ delivers an eye-catching colorway of the minimalist slip-on silhouette. The re-engineered Primeknit upper is rendered in a mix of mustard yellow and honeyed tan hues, while the translucent monofilament window is distinguished by an eye-catching neon green finish. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a grey rubber cage and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole. The Yeezy Boost 380 Kids 'Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 750 'Black' Sample
results.story: This blacked-out Yeezy Boost 750 Sample was unveiled in 2015 as the second-ever colorway following a two-tone grey version. The high-top silhouette’s suede construction is complemented by a matching midfoot canvas strap and Yeezy Boost midsole to give the shoe a tonal look.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ delivers a subdued rendition of the minimalist lifestyle sneaker. A charcoal grey finish dominates the re-engineered Primeknit upper, with inky black and a subtle streak of navy blue surrounding the translucent monofilament window. The sock-like build sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, encaged in semi-translucent rubber and supported underfoot by a herringbone traction outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Etham
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Sand’ delivers a monotone iteration of Kanye West’s clog-like silhouette. Featuring a slightly darker tan shade than the debut ‘Ararat’ colorway from 2020, the slip-on makes use of a flexible one-piece build that combines standard EVA with an algae-based foam compound. Multiple ventilation ports allow feet to breathe, while textured interiors offer no-slip grip. Underfoot, a classic herringbone tread provides dependable traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Chocolate
results.story: Released in October 2015 as part of Yeezy Season 1, the Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Chocolate’ features a silhouette that combines a duck boot with a military boot, wrapped up in a monochromatic build. The materials include rubber, ballistic mesh, and suede, all finished in the same dark brown palette. Exterior branding is limited to adidas and Yeezy wordmarks on the outsole, as well as the mismatched tongue tags.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Salt
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Salt’ follows a design trail originally blazed by the Yeezy 500 in November 2018. Like its predecessor, the lifestyle silhouette features a monochromatic light grey finish on a mesh base with tonal overlays in suede and leather. A sculpted midsole in matching grey, concealing full-length Boost cushioning within, features a subtle black accent, matched by the rubber outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Inertia
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Inertia’ is part of the Yeezy Season 8 lineup that launched March 2019. The ‘Inertia’ colorway showcases the original 700 upper, with a heavily paneled construction made with premium suede, mesh and smooth leather sections. Cast primarily in cool grey tones, the sneaker includes hits of Tangerine for contrast. The shoe’s signature chunky midsole is equipped with full-length Boost cushioning for responsive comfort.

results.name: Nike Roshe Run FB Yeezy
results.story: The Nike Roshe One FB ‘Yeezy’ features a distinctive color palette reminiscent of the brand’s Solar Red Air Yeezy 2 collaboration with Kanye West. The shoe’s black mesh upper is accented with a speckled Pink Flash Swoosh at the toe, while the tonal black quarter panels are finished in a subtle reptilian texture—a hallmark feature of the Air Yeezy 2. A final design tie-in takes the form of the Fresh Mint coloring on the lightweight sole unit.

results.name: Nike Solarsoft Moccasin Woven Yeezy
results.story: Part of a series of shoes inspired by the Chinese zodiac’s Year of the Snake, this Solarsoft Moc Woven features a premium leather upper with snakeskin detailing near the laces. The forefoot sports a woven detail reminiscent of the stitching of a moccasin, and the mesh tongue panel promotes breathability. The simple colorway of the exterior is contrasted by the Challenge Red inner lining.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Peyote
results.story: The Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Peyote’ was one of the four original colorways of the duck boot-military boot hybrid that launched as part of Kanye West’s Yeezy Season 1 range. The light tan hue is tonally consistent with the color story of the collection at large, which is highlighted by a dark and muddy palette. The rugged build makes use of a combination of ballistic mesh, suede and durable throughout the upper, while the outsole makes use of a high-traction rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Analog
results.story: Music and fashion icon Kanye West debuted the Yeezy Boost 700 at his Yeezy Season 5 fashion show in February 2017. This 'Analog' colorway released April 2019, and provides a monochromatic look to the acclaimed shoe. Dressed in shades of white, leather, mesh and suede panels come together to construct its upper. Down below, full-length Boost cushioning provides a responsive feel, built inside the 700's signature chunky midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Slate
results.story: Designer Kanye West updates the 500 silhouette with the adidas Yeezy 500 High. Launched in December 2019, this makeover is set up with a Slate-colored neoprene base overlaid in paneled suede with touches of tumbled leather. Rope laces secure the tongue and a textured mudguard reinforces the sidewall. Offering contrast, the sculpted midsole holds Adiprene cushioning and undulating tread patterns the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Arzareth’ features vibrant blue tones on a breathable knit upper, its side panels overlaid with a semi-translucent RPU cage for added structure and durability. Contrasting black is applied to the sneaker’s bootie-style collar, good for a snug fit around the ankle. The sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ utilizes a re-engineered Primeknit upper finished in muddy brown tones. A contrasting splash of royal blue distinguishes the translucent monofilament window that’s woven into the lateral side of the sock-like construction. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a fluid transition. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole provides grippy traction. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Europe.

results.name: Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy
results.story: Released in April of 2014, The Nike Air Foamposite Pro Prm 'Yeezy’ was inspired by Kanye West’s 2012 Nike Air Yeezy 2 NRG ‘Solar Red’ and features a design that combines a black mesh/nubuck upper with a black Foamposite shell and swoosh. The sneaker also includes bright solar red accents and sits on a glow-in-the-dark translucent green outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Infants 'Hylte'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Hylte’ dresses the sneaker’s re-engineered Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of tan and yellow hues, resulting in a subtle camo-like design that’s interrupted by a streak of neon green on the translucent monofilament window. The lightweight build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in grey rubber and reinforced by a herringbone rubber outsole to provide reliable traction for little feet. The Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Kyanite’ showcases flowing stripes of blue coloring throughout the breathable upper, constructed from monofilament engineered mesh with exoskeletal RPU overlays coated in a glow-in-the-dark finish. Interior bootie construction delivers a snug fit, while a reinforced rubber toe cap provides added durability. The sneaker rides on a lightweight EVA midsole encapsulated in an off-white PU cage, supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey
results.story: The adidas Yeezy PowerPhase is an expression of designer Kanye West's reverence for retro sportswear. Updated in September 2019, this Quiet Gray variation has a suede base minimally styled with perforated Three-Stripes, tonal lacing and a signature logo window. 'Calabasas' is spelled out in gold foil on the quarter panel. Its split rubber cupsole is kept standard to match the sneaker's single-hued scheme.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Simple Brown
results.story: In September 2019, the adidas Yeezy PowerPhase was reintroduced in a three colorway collection designed around Kanye West's trademark selection of earth tones. A Simple Brown shade is draped across this variation's suede upper, mesh lining and laces. Contrast comes from the retro logo window and metallic 'Calabasas' lettering alongside the Three-Stripes. The classic rubber cupsole is positioned below for support.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Triple Black'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 further showcases Kanye West's low-top sneaker design with a modified profile and technical motif. This 'Black' edition features a dark Primeknit upper with reflective elements, circular perforations and flecked laces. As established through previous Yeezy releases, this edition includes a full-length adidas Boost unit encapsulated within semi-translucent rubber. The shoe is finished with a tightly treaded outsole and a small Three-Stripes icon at the heel.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Desert Sand'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Desert Sand’ combines plush comfort with a futuristic, minimalist design, executed on a lightweight EVA build and finished in a refined hue. The unibody upper is stripped of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the cushioned footbed. An aggressive traction pattern distinguishes the outsole, delivering optimal grip and impact absorption underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil
results.story: Borrowing the suede toe box and oval overlays from the Yeezy 500, 2019's Yeezy Desert Boot 'Oil' takes Kanye West's signature line into boot territory. The three-quarter cut upper comes in a smooth suede and mesh, with thick rope laces and an exaggerated mudguard. The chunky foam midsole pairs with a thick rugged outsole for outdoors-ready cushioning and traction. The entire silhouette comes in an earth-toned motif, with just a bit of branding on the bottom of the sole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Light’ updates the minimalist sneaker with UV-sensitive technology, a first for Kanye West’s lifestyle imprint. Under artificial light, the Primeknit upper projects a subtle ivory finish. Exposure to direct sunlight yields soft pink coloring throughout the knit build, while the monofilament side stripe darkens to an amber hue. The color-shifting assembly is supported by a standard rubber-wrapped Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Mauve
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Mauve’ takes on a somber color scheme that blends black and purplish grey across its signature multi-layered upper. The complex arrangement sees different varieties of mesh complemented with suede and textured leather paneling, all resting upon a tonal sculpted midsole accented with pops of neon green. Exterior branding is limited to subtly visible Three-Stripes on the quarter panel and an adidas logo embossed on the outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper Non-Reflective’ applies a neutral color scheme to its breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a snug, sock-like fit that allows for a secure fit with or without laces. A muddy tan finish distinguishes the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, allowing the signature detail to stand out against a knit backdrop in lighter grey and Off-White tones. A full-length Boost midsole supports the lightweight build, equipped with a raised heel for a smooth ride.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Earth Brown'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slides Infants ‘Earth Brown’ applies a dull earth-tone finish to Kanye West’s lifestyle sandal. Built with lightweight EVA foam, the slip-on differs from its full-sized counterpart by adding a heel strap for a secure fit. Exaggerated flex grooves on the outsole deliver optimal traction and a cushioned ride. Branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo on the footbed, equipped with a soft top layer for step-in comfort.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Azael
results.story: Steering away from his previous retro-inspired slant, Kanye West explores future-facing design with the adidas Yeezy 700 V3. Unveiled in December 2019, this Azael edition receives a black neoprene bootie with a notched collar and striped textile underlay encased in a sculpted, open-work cage. Integrated lacing offers traditional lockdown.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Covellite’ showcases a mix of navy, indigo, and grey tones throughout the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The camo-like design is punctuated by perforated detailing that accompanies the sneaker’s semi-translucent monofilament window, woven into the side panel to enhance the breathability of the sock-like build. Responsive cushioning arrives via a caged full-length Boost midsole, featuring a stacked, elevated heel and supported underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Tactical Orange'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tactical Orange’ makes use of a ventilated brown mesh upper with contrasting suede overlays in varying shades of blue. A padded high-cut collar combines with a plush tongue to deliver a snug, comfortable fit, while a brown rubber mudguard offers lightweight support and abrasion-resistant durability. The bulky silhouette rests on a podular adiPRENE+ midsole, modeled after the adidas KB8 3 and finished in a subtle orange hue.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 350 Cleat Turtledove
results.story: The Yeezy 350 Cleat ‘Turtle Dove’ was first seen on the feet of Houston Texans Wide Receiver DeAndre Hopkins during week one of the 2016 NFL season. Released in September 2016, the cleat sold out by midday. The day after its release, the NFL fined Hopkins $6,000 for wearing the shoes and banned them due to them not having one dominant base color.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Earth Brown'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slides Kids ‘Earth Brown’ features a subdued monochromatic finish on Kanye West’s minimalist sandal. Built with lightweight EVA, the unibody build makes use of a single-strap setup with a soft top layer on the footbed, good for immediate step-in comfort and marked with adidas’ three-stripe branding. The slip-on rides atop an outsole equipped with exaggerated flex grooves that deliver enhanced traction with each step.

results.name: Yeezy 500 Infant 'Soft Vision'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Infant sneaker is a mix of retro inspiration and progressive design. Revealed in November 2019, this iteration expresses a Soft Vision palette in mesh, cow suede and premium leather with reflective piping around the eyelets. Its tonal mudguard offers abrasion resistance. A matching midsole imbued with Adiprene+ cushioning attenuates shock while the gum rubber outsole provides grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Non-Reflective’ features a contrasting blend of brown and slate hues on a breathable Primeknit upper designed to wrap around the foot in lightweight support. A yellow finish is applied to the translucent monofilament window that cuts through the lateral side, complete with a series of large perforations for enhanced air flow. Underfoot, cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole reveals the sneaker’s full-length Boost cushioning. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Non-Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Asia Pacific, Africa, the Middle East, and India.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White
results.story: The Yeezy 450 ‘Cloud White’ highlights neutral hues on a deconstructed sneaker developed with a design assist from Steve Smith, the mastermind behind iconic silhouettes ranging from the New Balance 997 to the Reebok Instapump Fury. Exterior branding is stripped from the one-piece knit textile upper, secured with an elastic cuff and an integrated lacing system. The minimalist design is encroached upon by the unique configuration of the molded outsole, featuring a set of ‘fingers’ that wrap up the side panels.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Eliada'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Eliada’ uses the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe to separate two distinct finishes on the sneaker’s Primeknit upper. The top portion utilizes a contrasting mix of coral and tan fibers, while the lower half features a tonal blend of brown and beige hues. The breathable knit build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber cage and reinforced with a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 'Mist Non-Reflective' utilizes a breathable Primeknit upper finished in a camo-like pattern comprising neutral grey and tan hues. Details include a sock-like collar, rope laces integrated directly into the knit build and perforated detailing on the side panels for ventilated comfort. A semi-translucent rubber cage is applied to the full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a forward-leaning stance. A gum rubber outsole is good for grippy traction underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Moonrock
results.story: The Yeezy 950 Boot 'Moonrock' features a textile upper dressed in a Moonrock color scheme with suede accents on the eyestay and tonal metal eyelets. The sneaker also sports a rounded toe for added comfort, a topstitched vamp, padded lining for a snug fit, and a heavy-duty rubber lug sole for impact protection and superior grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Utility Black
results.story: Kanye West and adidas launched the Yeezy 500 ‘Utility Black’ in July 2018. The retro-inspired silhouette counterbalances its bulky form with a sleek, all-black design. What sets this colorway apart from the standard triple-black finish is a singular use of tone – it’s a semi-faded black that coats the combination mesh and suede upper, as opposed to the pitch-black variety that’s more common in the sneaker firmament.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Barium’ makes use of a grey jacquard knit inlay reinforced with a translucent RPU cage on the side panels. A synthetic suede toe cap delivers added durability, while reflective detailing throughout the upper provides enhanced visibility in low-light conditions, including the seamless external heel counter. The midsole features a full-length Boost unit in a semi-translucent TPU cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Tyrian
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Tyrian’ makes use of a mixed-material build, featuring a purplish-blue elastane base with contrasting overlays in black leather and brown suede. A padded collar and tongue combine for a comfortable fit, while a rubber wrap at the base of the upper provides added durability and abrasion resistance. The podular midsole utilizes adiPRENE+ technology for impact absorption and high-rebound cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Infant ‘Alvah’ showcases a stealthy finish on this second colorway of the lifestyle silhouette. The upper blends a black and grey monofilament mesh upper with a glow-in-the-dark RPU exoskeleton for structural support. An interior bootie delivers a snug fit, while reflective detailing at the base of the tongue offers added visibility. The midsole is made with lightweight EVA, visible through cut-outs in the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Pepper Non-Reflective’ features subtle hues on a minimalist silhouette that does away with rigid structure and clearly defined lines. Instead, the sock-like Primeknit build highlights an amorphous, camo-like pattern, made up of beige and light grey hues that are contrasted by a splash of orange on the post-dyed monofilament side stripe. A full-length Boost midsole, confined within a greyish blue rubber cage, delivers a cushioned ride.

results.name: Nike Air Max 1 FB Yeezy
results.story: Released as part of the Football Pack, this Yeezy-inspired Air Max 1 colorway updates an iconic 1987 silhouette. The Air Max 1 FB 'Yeezy' features a black leather upper with mesh panels for ventilation and comfort and suede overlays for reinforcement. The sneaker also boasts Fresh Mint leather accents on the mudguard, a thick white midsole with a partially visible Flash Pink Air Max unit, embroidered branding at the heel and a woven tongue tab.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 'Carbon Blue' is a study of tonality inspired by previous 700 models. Debuted in December 2019, the sneaker is presented with a muted blue scheme across the upper's suede and nubuck panels with the tongue and laces in a bright tint. Grey tones for the mesh collar, perforated heel panel and leather eyestays anchor the palette. A sculpted midsole housing full-length Boost, with defined pops of color and dual-tone rubber outsole finish it off.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Zyon’ showcases various woven patterns on the breathable Primeknit upper, executed in a subdued blend of earth tones. The collar is trimmed in neutral grey, while the signature post-dyed monofilament stripe cuts through the sneaker’s lateral side in a dark brown finish. Full-length Boost cushioning is visible through the semi-translucent rubber midsole, reinforced underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Yecoraite Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Yecoraite’ carries a flexible Primeknit upper embellished with a camo-like pattern made up of neutral grey and off-white fibers. The minimalist sock-like build is accented with decorative laces and a translucent monofilament window in a pale orange hue. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber for improved stability and durability. A subtle coral finish is applied to the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy 500 'Super Moon Yellow' Sample
results.colorway: Super Moon Yellow/Super Moon Yellow/Super Moon Yellow

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Infants)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 Infant ‘Mist Non-Reflective’ is made for a new generation of Yeezy acolytes. The build is virtually identical to the sneaker’s full-sized counterpart, featuring a knit upper finished in a grey camo-like print. Tan laces are matched by a horizontal patch of color on the midfoot, which roughly aligns with perforated detailing for breathable comfort. The lightweight build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Kids ‘Cloud White’ highlights a subtle monochromatic finish on a futuristic sneaker designed with unique, eye-catching tooling.
