It takes the form of a molded EVA midsole that extends up the unstructured knit upper to create a supportive cage. An integrated lacing system secures the sock-like build, complete with an elastic cuff for easy on and off. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a wavy traction pattern and wide flex grooves for a smooth ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Cream
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 ‘Cream’ delivers an unassuming colorway of Kanye West’s running-inspired silhouette. The upper features rolled knit construction in a pale grey hue, reinforced with tonal no-sew skins and tan nubuck overlays. An off-white finish distinguishes the exaggerated EVA midsole, featuring sculpted sidewalls that conceal a full-length drop-in Boost unit. Underfoot, the rubber outsole uses a classic herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Earth
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Earth' makes use of a Primeknit upper in a monochromatic dark khaki hue, complete with a post-dyed monofilament side strip for textural variety and a textile heel tab for easy on and off. The midsole ditches the traditional semi-translucent look for sidewalls in opaque tan rubber, concealing full-length Boost cushioning housed within. A gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot. The 'Earth' colorway is available only in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Onyx Reflective’ makes use of a re-engineered Primeknit upper in a blend of black and mahogany tones. Semi-translucent woven construction distinguishes the post dyed monofilament side stripe that accents the lateral side panel, while reflective fibers add a high-vis element to the murky palette. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a smoky rubber cage and reinforced by a herringbone gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Solar Red
results.story: The Air Yeezy 2 NRG ‘Solar Red’ may share a familiar color palette with its Air Yeezy ‘Blink’ predecessor, but the newer model stands out with a more refined silhouette, accented with special details crafted specifically for Kanye. They include a molded rubber heel, anaconda textured side panel, and Egyptology references on the tongue and midfoot strap. One feature carried over from the original Air Yeezy is the glow-in-the-dark outsole, utilized here on tooling lifted from the Nike Air Tech Challenge II.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Utility Black
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700, designed by music and fashion icon Kanye West, first debuted at the Yeezy Season 5 fashion show in February 2017. This 'Utility Black' colorway from June 2019 sees the design in a mesh upper with both plush suede and smooth leather overlays. At the bottom, the Yeezy Boost 700's chunky midsole encapsulates adidas' revolutionary Boost cushioning in a full-length format, underscored by gum rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Phosphor’ showcases an eye-catching neon yellow finish on the polyester upper, accented with oversized reflective silver ‘700’ branding. Contrasting black no-sew overlays provide lightweight durability at the toe and heel, while no-tie bungee laces offer a secure fit. A webbing pull tab is good for easy on and off. The seamless upper rides on a sculpted black PU midsole, enhanced with full-length drop-in Boost cushioning.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Zen Grey
results.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Zen’ launched in April 2009, one of three colorways that made up the first collaborative release from Kanye West and Nike. An overall new silhouette with details borrowed from the Nike archives, the design employs a mostly neutral colorway with vibrantly hued accents throughout. The patent leather midfoot strap comes in a unique texture while the toe cap features premium suede. Underfoot, the nondescript rubber outsole glows green when the lights go down.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Yeezy
results.story: The Air Force 1 has lived through countless iterations since its initial release in the 1980s. In 2014, Nike released a stark colorway of the silhouette in a neon and black color scheme. The Air Force 1 'Yeezy' features a black nubuck-based upper with carbon fiber accents on the toe box and eyestay. The sneaker also sports Crimson accents on the Swoosh and inner lining, Arctic Green details on the outsole, and an encapsulated Air unit in the midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Teal Blue
results.story: Kanye West's approach to the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 results in a future-forward sneaker with a deft balance of athletic influence and progressive design intent. Debuted in October 2019, this update has a mesh, leather and suede upper in a predominantly muted palette interrupted by a Teal Blue forefoot and vibrant laces for visual impact. Its exaggerated Boost-filled midsole and gum rubber outsole enhance support and traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Israfil’ features a patchwork-like composition on the Primeknit upper, constructed from a two-tone blend of tan and grey yarns. The neutral hues are enlivened by a streak of yellow on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of the standard full-length Boost midsole, encased in a semi-translucent rubber sidewall. A grippy gum rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Frosted Blue’ showcases a contrasting two-tone color palette on a retro-inspired lifestyle sneaker that traces a lineage to the adidas KB8 III. The upper is composed of stretchy elastane in a vibrant blue finish, fortified with suede overlays in a lighter blue shade. They’re joined by tan suede on the sneaker’s segmented eyestay and reinforced toe wrap. Additional details include toggle lacing and a padded, high-cut collar. Cushioning arrives via a podular adiPRENE midsole that gives the nod to adidas’ Feet You Wear technology.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Earth'
results.story: Alongside its full-sized counterpart, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Earth’ launched exclusively in North America and Latin America in February 2020. A subdued light brown hue covers the breathable Primeknit upper, complete with a post-dyed monofilament side stripe for a see-through element and a textile pull tab at the heel for easy on and off. A ridged rubber midsole houses a full-length Boost unit for responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Moonrock (W)
results.story: Borrowing influence from the heritage duckboot, the Yeezy 950 Boot appears in a tonal ‘Moonrock’ color palette that’s built with a canvas fabric around the shaft, while suede accents on the eyestay add a premium finish. The mudguard and sole unit are equipped with a rubberized construction and a lugged outsole pattern.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Flax
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Flax' dons a breathable Primeknit upper in an understated wheat hue, complemented by tonal rope laces and a post-dyed monofilament side stripe tinted in a muted yellow finish. The lightweight knit build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, partially visible beneath a semi-translucent rubber cage with ridged detailing. The 'Flax' colorway is available only in Asia Pacific, Africa, India and the Middle East.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Tephra
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 V2 is the striking follow up to the Yeezy 700 which originally debuted at Kanye West's 2017 Yeezy Season 5 show. The V2 is more aerodynamic in appearance, with sleek, reflective overlays that draw the eye in. This rendition, the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 'Tephra' sneaker, features a mesh and suede upper with subdued natural tones, culminating in deeper hues on the midsole. This version reprises the 700's chunky sole, concealing full-length adidas Boost cushioning, underscored by gum-rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Shale Warm
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Wakaran’ showcases neutral beige tones on a flexible elastane upper, equipped with a comfortable padded collar and reinforced with suede and leather overlays. Reflective piping delivers added visibility in low-light conditions. Progressively darker shades of grey distinguish the podular adiPRENE+ midsole and rubber outsole, featuring a wavy traction pattern for optimal grip. The exterior is stripped of distinguishing logos and trademarks, relegating the sneaker’s branding elements to the sockliner instead.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kids ‘Safflower’ presents a subtle colorway of the sleek silhouette, highlighted by flowing yellow lines throughout the monofilament engineered mesh upper. The lightweight build is reinforced with a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage for added support and durability, while a contrasting black interior bootie provides a snug, one-to-one fit. An ivory hue coats the PU encapsulated EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Net Tan
results.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Net’ launched in June 2009 and would be the third and final colorway of the debut sneaker from Kanye West and Nike to hit stores. The shoe features a beige leather upper stopping at a high collar lined in pink, mounted on a two-tone midsole borrowed from the Nike Air Jordan 3. The smooth and glossy finish on the patent leather midfoot strap is contrasted by a perforated leather vamp and suede toe wrap, embossed with an all-over ‘Y’ print.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Turtle (W)
results.story: Released alongside Yeezy Season 1, the women’s Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Turtle Dove’ blends elements of a classic duck boot with a military boot. The seven-hole silhouette sports a combination textile and suede upper, accented with a long pull-tab on the heel and Yeezy-branded tonal suede tongue tags. Underfoot, the rubber lug outsole is embossed with dual adidas and Yeezy logos.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Quantum Infants ‘Teal Blue’ features the same minimalist build utilized on the men’s release. The one-piece Primeknit upper combines a neutral grey base with black and teal accents, along with reflective silver threads that form wavy lines along the side panel. A two-tone heel cap provides more reflectivity while also cradling the back of the foot. A semi-translucent cage surrounding the full-length Boost midsole delivers a stable ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Hyperspace
results.story: The first adidas Yeezy 350 V2 release of 2019 gets colored up in a pale blue/green hue for a clean, neutral upper incorporating a semi-translucent vent at the lateral side that matches up with the translucent outsole. This ‘Hyperspace’ edition features a flexible Primeknit upper and full-length Boost cushioning—both iconic features of the Yeezy 350 V2 sneaker. This shoe released March 2019 exclusively in select cities in Africa, the Middle East, India and Asia Pacific.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Clay’ updates the silhouette with a warm palette and semi-translucent, three-tone vent at the side. This ‘Clay’ colorway retains the stand-out features of the original 350 V2 shoe, first seen in September 2016, including a flexible Primeknit upper and full-length Boost cushioning. This shoe released March 2019 exclusively in select cities in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Fade
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Fade’ makes use of a patterned Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of beige and brown tones. The sneaker’s post-dyed monofilament side stripe is treated to an indigo finish, offering added breathability and a subtle pop of color. Standard adidas Boost cushioning is utilized on the midsole, entirely wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage for improved support and stability. This colorway is exlusive to the Asia-Pacific region

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Natural
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Natural’ presents an understated colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, featuring a stretchy Primeknit upper in a blend of varying cream and beige tones. On the sneaker’s lateral side, a post-dyed monofilament side stripe adds a see-through element to the lightweight build. Details include no-tie bungee laces and adidas’ three-stripe branding on the interior heel. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a yellow-tinted rubber cage, delivers a responsive ride.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Red October
results.story: The Air Yeezy 2 SP ‘Red October’ stands out from its two companion colorways. There’s the monochromatic scarlet finish, contrasted only by metallic gold lace tips. There’s the unique design, which sees the side panels ditch the standard anaconda texture in favor of rows upon rows of small triangular studs. Finally, there’s the chaos that surrounded the shoe’s much-delayed release. By the time the Red Octobers finally launched online with no advance notice in February 2014, Kanye West had already severed all ties with Nike.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Reflective’ showcases a pop of color on an otherwise subdued design, highlighted by a splash of royal blue on the signature translucent monofilament window. The rest of the upper is rendered in brown Primeknit, which weaves in reflective fibers for added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber and reinforced with a herringbone traction outsole underfoot. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Europe.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ showcases a camo-like design made up of black and dark brown fibers on the minimalist knit upper, secured with no-tie laces for easy on and off. The lightweight build is mostly unchanged from the men’s edition, featuring a post-dyed monofilament side stripe on the lateral side and a wrapped Boost midsole underfoot. A herringbone traction pattern on the gum rubber outsole provides optimal grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Clay Brown’ makes use of a monofilament engineered mesh upper in a mostly black finish, accented with swooping brown stripes that extend across the side panels. They’re visible in the open spaces of the RPU cage that adds structure — and a distinctly futuristic aesthetic — to the sneaker’s bootie-like construction. The bulky EVA midsole is encapsulated in a durable PU wrap and reinforced by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy (GS)
results.story: This Yeezy-inspired colorway of the Little Posite Pro came to the grade school lineup in 2014. Black Foamposite material makes up the majority of the upper alongside a textured leather tongue and eyestay panels. Colorful hits include red branding on the toe, heel, and sock liner.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Trfrm
results.story: Featuring a combination of neutral and earth tones, the adidas Yeezy 350 V2 ‘True Form’ is the first 350 colorway released in 2019. A soft grey hue dominates the flexible Primeknit upper with a small hit of orange behind the translucent vent on the lateral side that extends to the heel pull tab. Another hint of orange can be seen behind the ribbed TPU midsole, which houses full-length Boost cushioning. This shoe released March 2019 exclusively in select countries within Europe, as well as Russia and Ukraine.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Marsh
results.story: A Yeezy Supply-exclusive colorway, Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Marsh' makes use of a breathable Primeknit upper in an understated shade of yellow. A darker mustard yellow is applied to the sneaker’s elastic collar, while the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe is rendered with light grey fibers. The semi-translucent rubber outsole is similarly tinted yellow and packs a full-length Boost unit for responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Linen
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Linen’ showcases a pale yellow hue on the sneaker’s breathable Primeknit upper, accented with reflective detailing on the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe. The lining, as well as the reinforced trim around the collar, are both finished in slate blue coloring. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, encapsulated in semi-translucent rubber cage and supported underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Synth'
results.story: Released regionally in June 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Synth' sneaker represents Kanye West's progressive, nonconformist design aesthetic. Patterned rope laces and a signature monofilament stripe are integrated into the sneaker's two-tone Primeknit bootie. The Three-Stripes emblem adorns the interior heel. A tubular sole powered by Boost technology helps ensure a comfortable step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Super Moon Yellow
results.colorway: Super Moon Yellow/Super Moon Yellow/Super Moon Yellow
results.story: The Yeezy 500 Super Moon Yellow arrives in a  light  yellow finish on the suede and mesh upper with a midsole inspired by the adidas ‘Feet You Wear’ technology of the ‘90s. Befitting the shoe’s unique moniker, the original December 2017 launch of the Yeezy 500 ‘Super Moon Yellow’ was wholly unconventional: shoppers were able to get their hands on the kicks only if they purchased a bundled option that also included a hoodie and sweat shorts. A subsequent standalone release followed months later.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Infants ‘Frozen Blue’ presents a vibrant colorway of Kanye West’s futuristic basketball-inspired sneaker, scaled down and simplified for little feet. No-tie laces secure an a layered knit jacquard upper, enlivened with flowing blue lines that extend from the synthetic suede toe cap to the black neoprene heel/collar. A seamless heel counter extends to the caged Boost midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 MNVM 'Bright Cyan'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bright Cyan’ makes use of a lightweight polyester upper, secured with no-tie bungee laces and finished in a vibrant aqua hue. No-sew overlays provide lightweight durability and support, while reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker’s signature ‘700’ branding adorns the lateral side. Responsive cushioning arrives via sculpted PU midsole, housing full-length Boost cushioning within and reinforced with a herringbone-tread outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Mist Slate
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Mist’ delivers an understated colorway of the retro-inspired silhouette that borrows tooling from Kobe Bryant’s KB8 3, itself modeled after the brand’s Feet You Wear cushioning technology. Up top, grey elastane is fortified with tonal suede and leather overlays that reveal a subtle greenish cast. Reflective piping traces the wavy lines of the mudguard, while a grey rubber wrap provides added durability. A matching grey adiPRENE+ midsole delivers impact absorption and a smooth ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 V2 ‘Static’ is an update to the original Wave Runner. The upper features a slightly reworked design, while the midsole stays the same. This new edition showcases an understated colorway made up of soft, neutral shades. The layered composition of the upper, featuring a mesh base with welded reflective overlays and leather paneling, is finished in varying shades of grey and white. The silhouette’s signature bulky midsole, finished in matching white, is supported underfoot by a black rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga
results.story: Unveiled at the Yeezy Season 3 presentation at Madison Square Garden, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Beluga’ dropped on September 24, 2016. The evolved Yeezy Boost 350 V2 silhouette features a two-tone grey Primeknit and a solar red stripe with SPLY-350 branding on the lateral side. On the medial side, the suede midfoot panel has been removed and the pull tab replaced with a new elastic fit.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN ‘Bone’ makes use of a high-contrast color scheme, highlighted by a cream polyester upper with black no-sew overlays at the toe and heel. No-tie bungee laces provide easy on and off, while reflective 700 branding on the sneaker’s quarter panel offers added visibility in low-light conditions. The seamless build rests on a sculpted black PU midsole, which houses drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Cinder Non-Reflective’ delivers a muted colorway of Kanye West’s popular lifestyle silhouette. A charcoal grey hue is applied throughout the Primeknit upper, accented with the standard post-dyed monofilament stripe on the sneaker’s lateral side. The same dark grey coloring is used on the rubber cage that encapsulates the Boost midsole, while the outsole is rendered in grippy gum rubber. Underfoot, an unexpected pop of bright yellow distinguishes the heel pod.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Pirate Black
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 950 Boot is a triple fusion of three classic silhouettes. Unveiled in October 2015, this 'Pirate' edition mirrors a combat and duck boot with a nylon and textile upper and weatherized laces. A rear pull tab aids entrance, while a debossed tongue label authenticates the look. Elevated by a high-profile midsole, the aggressive, hiking-inspired tread designates the style for sartorial performance.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Teal Blue’ makes use of a Primeknit upper in a subtle palette of grey, black and teal. Silver reflective thread is woven into the side panels, forming wavy lines that provide added visibility in low-light conditions. A two-tone heel cap is similarly rendered in reflective finish, while matte black neoprene is utilized on the collar and tongue. The minimalist build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent rubber for improved stability.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra
results.story: Released on February 25, 2017, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Zebra’ combines a white/core black Primeknit upper with red SPLY 350 branding and a translucent white midsole housing full-length Boost. Sold exclusively at adidas.com, Yeezy Supply, and select adidas flagship stores, the ‘Zebra’ sold out instantly but was restocked on June 24th, 2017. Another restock of the ‘Zebra’ arrived November 16, 2018, with more pairs hitting the marketplace and delivering on Kanye’s promise of Yeezy’s being more accessible to anyone that wanted them.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Calcite Glow
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Calcite Glow’ highlights a neutral combination of white and grey tones on the breathable Primeknit upper, complete with camo-like glow-in-the-dark detailing that’s revealed when the lights go out. A dark grey finish distinguishes the translucent monofilament window on the sneaker’s side panel, matching the sock-like collar that provides a snug fit around the ankle. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 symbolizes a redux of the layered V1 aesthetic with its exaggerated proportions and intricate construction. Unveiled in September 2019 and mirroring a V1 colorway, this Inertia edition softens the icon with a monochromatic mesh, suede and synthetic film upper. Silver reflective accents settle on the heel. With color-pop detailing, the sculpted Boost midsole rides on top of a herringbone-patterned gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Oxford Tan’ features an oxford/light stone Primeknit upper with tonal oxford laces, suede patches on the medial sides, and a tan Boost outsole. First worn by Kanye at the August 2015 MTV VMAs, the fourth colorway of the Yeezy 350 was released at select adidas Originals Retail stores on December 29th, 2015.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Geode
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 ‘Geode’ sneaker pairs varying shades of grey with bold, reflective elements. This ‘Geode’ colorway showcases the updated 700 V2 upper, constructed with breathable mesh, premium leather and rich suede panels. The shoe’s laces, quarter and heel panels incorporate high-vis detailing, bringing contrast to the design. The 700’s recognizable chunky midsole is unaltered, offering the responsive feel of full-length adidas’ Boost cushioning sitting atop a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Butter
results.story: Kanye West and adidas continued their partnership with the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Butter,’ which hit stores in June 2018. The minimalist silhouette features distinct center stitching on a reverse Primeknit upper, with the signature ‘SPLY-350’ inscription now printed on the interior side. The heel tab remains, finished in a bright yellow hue that matches the knitted upper, rope laces, and Boost-infused midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Yecoraite Reflective (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Yecoraite’ applies a subtle palette to a sock-like upper entirely constructed from flexible Primeknit. A camo-like pattern made up of grey and off-white tones is contrasted by the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, which enlivens the sneaker’s lateral side panel with pale orange coloring and a unique see-through element. The full-length Boost midsole is wrapped in semi-translucent rubber and reinforced with a coral herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Pepper Non-Reflective’ delivers a subtle colorway of the minimalist lifestyle sneaker for little feet. The multi-toned Primeknit upper, featuring a camo-like pattern in light grey and beige hues, offers a snug, sock-like fit. Semi-translucent orange mesh is woven into the monofilament window, adding enhanced air flow and a flash of color. Soft cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange
results.story: Kanye West brought together legendary designers Christian Tresser and Steven Smith for the adidas 700 MNVN. The sneaker's classic construction is ditched for an orange padded nylon upper complete with heat-welded overlays, a new heel tab and an oversized reflective '700' logo graphic across the lateral, omitting Three-Stripes branding. A black Boost-infused midsole is matched up with a herringbone rubber outsole. The 700 MNVN ‘Orange’ release was available only in select stores in two cities: Los Angeles and Paris.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta
results.story: Seen as the successor to the first Yeezy 700 that debuted at Kanye West’s 2017 Yeezy Season 5 show, the Yeezy Boost 700 V2 sneaker maintains elements of the original while updating it with a sleeker profile. Released in June 2019, the 'Vanta' edition brings an all-over black hue to its multi-layered mesh upper with suede overlays. Below, full-length adidas Boost technology cushions the foot, encapsulated within the 700's distinct chunky sole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Infants ‘Safflower’ overlays a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage atop a monofilament engineered mesh upper that’s shot through with flowing yellow lines. A contrasting black bootie and matching laces offer a comfortable fit for little feet, while the PU encapsulated EVA midsole delivers lightweight cushioning with each step. Underfoot, the rubber outsole utilizes a classic herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow
results.story: Regarded as a cultural phenomenon, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 silhouette generated a cult following when it was initially released in 2015. This ‘Glow’ makeover—released in May 2019—equips the Primeknit upper with a high-visibility treatment and a translucent stripe to the lateral profile. Integrated lacing and a coordinating heel pull provide easy on/off. Underfoot, the signature full-length Boost midsole looks to the future with a bright glow in the dark finish.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White
results.story: As of late the YEEZY Boosts have been the driving force behind Kanye West’s and adidas’ ongoing collaboration. But in early-mid 2017 a non-Boost sneaker collaboration had the internet buzzing - the ‘80s inspired adidas YEEZY Powerphase ‘Calabasas’. These sneakers feature an Off-White buttery leather that enhances the sneakers vintage vibe.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Taupe Blue
Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Cinder'
results.story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black
results.story: Kanye teased the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Black’ colorway in a February 2015 interview with New York’s Power 105.1 FM. Later he was spotted wearing a black suede/gum sole iteration of the sneaker at a Givenchy show during New York Fashion Week. Released on December 19, 2015, as the second colorway of the Yeezy Boost 750 line, the ‘Black’ sneaker features a full suede upper, perforated vamp, and ankle zipper.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Infant ‘Cloud White’ presents the debut colorway of a futuristic Yeezy model scaled down for little feet. Decorative no-tie stretch laces are integrated into the flexible knit upper, featuring an elastic cuff for a sock-like fit. A molded EVA midsole combines with an Ortholite sockliner to deliver lightweight cushioning, while its unique structure forms a supportive cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a wavy traction pattern for added grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Yecoraite Reflective (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Yecoraite’ offers sock-like comfort for little feet, featuring a Primeknit upper equipped with decorative no-tie laces and a snug, elastic collar. A blend of grey and off-white tones is contrasted by a translucent monofilament window in a diluted orange hue. The minimalist silhouette sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, enveloped in a semi-translucent rubber cage and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole in a subtle coral finish.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Mist Non-Reflective’ features a breathable Primeknit upper finished in varying grey shades that form an all-over camo-like pattern. An elastic collar delivers a snug fit, while perforated detailing increases ventilation on the side panel, which is further highlighted by a semi-translucent patch of tan coloring. The tooling consists of a responsive Boost midsole, reinforced with a durable gum rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum
results.story: The Air Yeezy 2 NRG 'Pure Platinum' launched in June 2012 featuring a subdued colorway that blends varying shades of grey on the upper and a contrasting pop of bright red on the collar lining. The unique design allows it to straddle the line between fashion and sport. The snakeskin texture on the side panels and prominent ridges on the molded rubber heel serve to elevate the design, but the Air Tech Challenge II midsole keeps the shoe grounded in the heritage of the Swoosh.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘LMNTE Reflective’ adds a hi-vis element to Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, featuring slip-on construction designed to hug the foot in lightweight support. Reflective threads are woven into the mostly brown Primeknit upper, accented with mustard yellow coloring throughout the translucent monofilament window. The minimalist build is mounted atop a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent cage for added durability. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Asia Pacific, Africa, the Middle East, and India.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Clay'
results.story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper Reflective’ offers sock-like comfort on the upper, crafted from subtly patterned Primeknit in a blend of light grey and beige hues. Reflective fibers are woven into the mix, offering enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A coppery finish distinguishes the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, adding a see-through element to the minimalist build. A greyish-blue rubber cage envelops the full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (Infant)
results.story: Released on August 24th, 2016, alongside the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Pirate Black’ 2016 colorway, the Yeezy Boost 350 Infant ‘Turtle Dove’ is an exact replica of the adult model in infant sizes from 5 to 10. The design features a blue-gray/turtle dove Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a white Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core Black
results.story: Designed by Kanye West, the Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas 'Core Black' is a minimalist take on adidas' Powerphase sneaker from the 80s. Dressed in an all-black leather upper with matching laces, the lateral side is accented by gold ‘Calabasas’ print and green 'adidas' text alongside a red Trefoil logo. A black EVA midsole and rubber outsole complete the look. Released as part of the 'Calabasas' collection, other colorways include 'Core White' and 'Grey'.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Alien Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Alien Blue’ delivers a wintry colorway of the lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a grey and cream Primeknit upper with reflective detailing for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A subtle green finish distinguishes the monofilament window that adds textural depth to the sneaker’s lateral side panel. The sock-like build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent blue rubber cage and supported by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ offers a subdued colorway of the minimalist silhouette, featuring a composition of black and dark brown fibers that make up the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is interrupted on the sneaker’s lateral side, where a post dyed monofilament side stripe sweeps through the midfoot. A smokey rubber cage envelops the Boost midsole, visible through cut-outs in the gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Mist'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sesame
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sesame’ features a refined color palette that complements the shoe’s minimalist build. The breathable Primeknit upper keeps the heel tab and distinct center stitch detailing but loses the mirrored ‘SPLY-350’ branding. Underneath, a semi-translucent rubber midsole houses a full-length Boost cushioning, while a gum rubber outsole delivers enhanced traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kids ‘Alvah’ features a subdued color scheme, highlighted by a black monofilament mesh upper with flowing grey stripes. An exoskeletal overlay in glow-in-the-dark RPU provides structure to the sneaker’s side panels, while a rubberized toe cap is good for lightweight durability. Reflective detailing offers added visibility at the base of the tongue. In lieu of Boost cushioning, the sneaker uses a bulky EVA midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an energetic color scheme made up of yellow and tan hues throughout the re-engineered Primeknit upper. The resulting camo-like design is treated to a green-tinged glow-in-the-dark finish, matching the dayglow shade applied to the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window. The bright tones are tempered by the midsole, featuring full-length Boost encased in dark grey rubber. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Bright Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Bright Blue’ uses sharply contrasting finishes to delineate the lifestyle runner’s upper and tooling. The latter pairs sculpted orange sidewalls with a contrasting black rubber outsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern with cut-out detailing that reveals a drop-in Boost midsole. Up top, royal blue mesh is reinforced with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel, along with black suede midfoot panels enlivened with reflective detailing.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Synth'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Synth' sneaker is characterized by minimalist design principles and progressive cues as envisioned by Kanye West. Regionally launched in June 2019, this edition's duo-tone Primeknit upper features patterned rope laces and a transparent stripe on the lateral side. Three-Stripes detailing is seen at the interior heel. A Boost-encapsulated tubular sole optimizes impact support.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum Kids ‘Frozen Blue’ injects a vibrant dose of color to the basketball-inspired silhouette, highlighted by a bright blue RPU cage overlaid across the jacquard knit upper. Black neoprene is utilized on the collar and tongue to deliver a comfortable fit, while a seamless heel counter provides rearfoot stability. The mid-top rides on a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent TPU cage and reinforced with a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Carbon’ features a breathable Primeknit upper in a neutral black and grey finish. The sneaker’s lateral side features a streak of black via the post-dyed monofilament side stripe, separating a light grey weave up top with mostly black construction on the lower half. No-tie bungee laces deliver a secure fit. The sneaker rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a yellow-tinged rubber cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Non-Reflective’ utilizes a sock-like Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of beige and orange tones. The sneaker’s signature translucent monofilament window stands out in a contrasting blue finish, complete with perforated detailing for improved breathability. The one-piece build rides on a full-length Boost midsole, surrounded by a semi-translucent cage and reinforced by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids pulls iconic technology from the German brand's archives, packaging them into a retro-influenced sneaker driven by Kanye West's design ethos. Arrived in August 2019, this edition is crafted of Bone White mesh, cow suede and leather. Reinforced laces and reflective piping around the eyelets hint at a utilitarian aesthetic. An AdiPRENE+ midsole and rubber outsole supply cushioning and grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM BSKTBL Frozen Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Basketball ‘Frozen Blue’ highlights a pop of color on the performance-ready version of Kanye West’s futuristic hoops shoe. The upper features textile knit construction reinforced with RPU overlays, their raised wavy lines traced with vibrant blue coloring. Extra padding is added to the black neoprene collar, reinforced with a seamless heel counter that extends to a full-length Boost midsole encaged in semi-translucent TPU. Underfoot, a herringbone traction rubber outsole provides optimal grip on the hardwood.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2015)
results.story: Released on August 22nd, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Pirate Black’ features a pirate black/dark gray Primeknit upper with branded suede patches on the medial sides, patterned dark grey rope laces, red accented heel tabs, and a black Boost outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Blue Oat Reflective’ makes use of a Primeknit upper in a blend of orange and brown hues, resulting in a unique camo-like pattern that’s enlivened with a contrasting pop of blue on the translucent monofilament window. Reflective thread is woven into the sock-like build, offering added visibility in low-light conditions. The responsive Boost midsole is encased in semi-translucent rubber and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 'Vanta' was offered up in this infant-sized iteration for a June 2019 release. The shoe features a futuristic, multi-layer mesh upper with suede overlays, just like the larger sizes. The Yeezy 700 V2 features a similar chunky midsole compared to the V1, which debuted at Kanye West's Season 5 fashion show in 2017. The midsole houses full-length adidas Boost cushioning for responsive comfort.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Infant)
results.story: Debuting in late March, 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Clay' marked the first time a 350 would be released in adult, kids and infant sizes. The infant-sized Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Clay' mimics the larger versions, with a Primeknit upper that features a variety of patterns in orange-brown with a horizontal contrast stripe. A bright orange heel tab adds an accent, and the silhouette sits atop a translucent midsole and rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Carbon’ delivers a neutral colorway of the slip-on sneaker, secured with no-tie bungee laces for a snug fit. The upper makes use of breathable Primeknit in a mostly black finish with varying shades of grey throughout. On the lateral side, a black monofilament side stripe cuts through the two-tone woven paneling. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, encased entirely in semi-translucent rubber.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Zyon’ delivers a neutral colorway of Kanye West’s lifestyle sneaker, highlighted by complementary grey and brown tones on a stretchy Primeknit upper. Traditional lace closure enhances the fit of the slip-on silhouette, while a black monofilament side stripe provides added breathability. The lightweight build rests on a full-length Boost midsole, visible through cut-out detailing on the rubber midsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Citrin Non-Reflective'
results.story: Defining an era, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is the manifestation of Kanye West's unique design methodology and cultural influence. This 'Citrin' version—launched in September 2019—carries a dual-tone Primeknit bootie and tonal cord laces. Translucent monofilament panels are inserted into the sides while the back heel pull is removed for this colorway. Its distinctive TPU ribbed rubber sole, encasing Boost cushioning, is updated with a contrast tread pattern.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Kids)
results.story: Issued in May 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 GID Kids 'Glow' sneaker remixes the unconventional icon with updated functionality. The Primeknit bootie illuminates in the dark as a result of a fluorescent green treatment. Rope laces, a signature heel pull and a translucent monofilament stripe on the lateral side give the shoe its distinctive look. results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant ‘Desert Sage’ applies a military-inspired color scheme to the minimalist lifestyle silhouette, highlighted by a bright pop of orange on a subtle green knit upper. Reflective thread is woven into the monofilament side stripe for added visibility in low-light conditions. Secured with traditional lace closure, the lightweight build rides on a Boost midsole, encased in semi-translucent green rubber.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey
results.story: This inaugural colorway of Kanye West’s Yeezy Wave Runner 700 launched in November 2017, following a public debut earlier in the year as part of the Yeezy Season 5 runway show. The sneaker’s retro-inspired lines worked in tandem with a chunky silhouette reminiscent of an earlier era. A mesh base is finished in grey on the quarter panels and bright blue and teal on the forefoot. Suede overlays arrive on the toe and heel accented grey leather eyestays. Other details include neon green laces, a bulky white midsole, and pops of black and bright orange.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Non Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Lundmark Non-Reflective' offers a modern-neutral take on Kanye West's 350 silhouette that debuted in 2015. The 'Lundmark' model features a cream-colored Primeknit upper with a translucent window along the lateral. Notably, this shoe does without the heel-tab that has been a staple on previous Yeezy Boost 350 releases. At the bottom, the sneaker's full-length adidas Boost cushioning is encapsulated within a TPU cage that extends from the midsole down to the outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 750 'Glow in the Dark' Sample
results.story: This sample pair of the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Glow in the Dark’ features a grey suede upper and gum rubber sole unit—a muted color scheme that’s in line with the prevailing Yeezy aesthetic. Details include a wide midfoot strap, perforated toe box and concealed zipper for easy on and off. The high-top is finished with a glow-in-the-dark sole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Red’ released alongside ‘Copper’ and ‘Green’ colorways on November 23, 2016. Like its companions, this pair features mostly black Primeknit construction, accented with contrast-hued fibers resulting in a speckled effect throughout the upper. The sneaker’s lateral side is embellished with a bright red stripe that extends from heel to toe, marked with SPLY-350 branding. Responsive cushioning arrives via a caged Boost midsole, visible through cut-away detailing on the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Green
results.story: Released on November 23, 2016, in a three-pack alongside the ‘Copper’ and ‘Red,’ the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Green’ combines a black Primeknit upper with a green stripe, SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent black midsole housing full-length Boost.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Non-Reflective)
results.story: Released in December 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yecheil' sneaker departs from Kanye West's previous renditions connected by his signature earth tones. Multicolored yarns give a graphical look to the Primeknit upper. Classic features include rope laces, Three-Stripes at the inner heel and a translucent monofilament stripe through the lateral. The same 350 midsole/outsole is blacked out and still houses full-length Boost cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static (Non-Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Static Non-Reflective’ is designed to stand out, thanks to the addition of never-before-seen features. They include a translucent side stripe and 3M reflective detailing on the shoe’s rope laces, Primeknit upper and Three-Stripes branding on the interior heel. The midsole makes use of ridged TPU sidewalls with semi-translucent properties, revealing full-length adidas Boost cushioning within.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Non-Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneaker was first revealed at the Yeezy Season 3 fashion show and released in September 2016. The 'Antlia Non-Reflective' model reprises the design, covering the shoe's Primeknit upper with a pale yellow-green hue. A translucent stripe lines the lateral side, which leads to the back where the traditional heel tab has been removed. This region-exclusive colorway released June 2019 alongside a similar 'Reflective' version. As is standard in all Boost 350 models, full-length adidas Boost cushioning is encapsulated in a wrapped TPU shell that extends from the midsole to the outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Non-Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 lives up to its cult appeal through evolved design elements and advanced technology. Released June 2019, this ‘Black Non-Reflective' edition's re-engineered Primeknit bootie sees futuristic updates including a translucent side stripe and bold stitching on the heel pull. Integrated lacing customizes the fit while a translucent black Boost-equipped midsole complements the covert feel.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Infant)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infants ‘Ash Pearl’ outfits a scaled-down version of the sock-like sneaker in a neutral-hued Primeknit upper. The lateral side is rendered in split color blocking, featuring a blend of subtle tan shades across the vamp, collar and monofilament side stripe. They’re joined by a greyscale finish on the lower portion of the shoe, and throughout the medial side in an uninterrupted patchwork arrangement. A rubber-wrapped Boost midsole offers a cushioned ride.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Brown Gum (Chocolate)
results.story: First seen during Kanye’s Yeezy Season 2 presentation at New York Fashion Week, the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘Chocolate’ sneaker was officially released a month later on October 15, 2016. The design combines a light brown nubuck upper with an elasticated mid-foot strap, perforated vamp, and a gum Boost midsole that glows in the dark. The sneaker also features an upgraded YKK ankle zipper.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Copper
results.story: Released on November 23, 2016, in a three-pack alongside the ‘Green’ and ‘Red’ colorways, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Copper’ combines a black Primeknit upper with a Copper stripe, SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent black midsole housing full-length Boost.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Semi Frozen Yellow
results.story: Kanye West’s Yeezy Boost 350 V2 in Semi Frozen Yellow first hit stores in November 2017, with a restock that released on December 14, 2018. Dressed in adidas’ signature Primeknit upper, the lifestyle runner is finished in an energetic bright yellow hue, one that extends to the laces, heel tab, and Boost-infused ribbed rubber midsole. Zebra-like black stripes add another design dimension to the upper, along with a tonal side stripe emblazoned with ‘SPLY 350’ in reverse red print. A gum rubber outsole adds grippy traction to the eye-catching design.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sulfur Welcome Offer
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Sulfur’ utilizes a breathable Primeknit upper in a yellowish tan hue, accented with the sneaker’s signature monofilament side stripe in olive green. A pull tab at the heel complements the sock-like collar to deliver easy on and off. Underneath the foot, a full-length Boost unit provides responsive cushioning. The foam compound is visible through cut-out detailing on the gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids ‘Ash Pearl’ shows off split color blocking on a sock-like upper constructed from breathable Primeknit. The top-down view reveals a visible seam that runs down the vamp, separating varying tan and grey shades on the lateral and medial sides. The former is accented with a monofilament side stripe, which gives way to more grey tones on the lower portion of the shoe. Decorated with no-tie elastic laces, the upper is mounted atop full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Reflective)
results.story: Kanye West eschewed traditional construction when he created the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2, realizing a forward-thinking aesthetic through his own industrial design approach. This edition—launched in September 2019—utilizes a two-tone Primeknit bootie with select reflectivity and a translucent lateral stripe. Carrying energy-filled Boost technology, its signature sole features a milky translucent finish and a grooved tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream/Triple White
results.story: First released on April 29, 2017, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Cream White’ combines a cream Primeknit upper with tonal cream SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent white midsole housing full-length Boost. Released again in October 2018, this retro helped fulfill Kanye West’s oft-repeated ‘YEEZYs for everyone’ Twitter mantra, as adidas organized the biggest drop in Yeezy history by promising pre-sale to anyone who signed up on the website. Similar to the first release, the ‘Triple White’ 2018 model features a Primeknit upper, a Boost midsole and custom adidas and Yeezy co-branding on the insole.

results.name: Air Yeezy 'Glow In The Dark Tour' Sample
results.story: A prototype of the Nike Air Yeezy, this colorway was first seen on the feet of Kanye West during his 2008 'Glow In The Dark' world concert tour. This unreleased style is outfitted in Anthracite dual-textured leather with a glossy midfoot strap, Swoosh cutouts and grey suede accents. A translucent pod secures the laces and the music icon's name is embroidered on the pull tab. Its red Air-infused midsole and rubber outsole are borrowed from the Air Jordan 3.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Infant)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant maintains the distinctive elements of Kanye West's pioneering design inspired by adidas' heritage. Unveiled in September 2019, this non-reflective Cloud White kid's iteration is realized in Primeknit with an asymmetrical, two-tone stitch pattern, lacing integrated into the tongue and a signature translucent stripe on the lateral side. The midsole is filled with energy-returning Boost technology.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Non-Reflective)
results.story: Defining an era, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is the manifestation of Kanye West's unique design methodology and cultural influence. This 'Citrin' version—launched in September 2019—carries a dual-tone Primeknit bootie and tonal cord laces. Translucent monofilament panels are inserted into the sides while the back heel pull is removed for this colorway. Its distinctive TPU ribbed rubber sole, encasing Boost cushioning, is updated with a contrast tread pattern.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeezreel (Non-Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeezreel Non-Reflective' communicates Kanye West's idiosyncratic design approach in a high-visibility look. Emerging in December 2019, the sneaker is delivered in a tri-colored Primeknit bootie toting bright rope laces, a translucent monofilament stripe across the lateral and a rear pull tab with distinctive red stitching. A neon Tubular rubber sole reveals full-length energetic Boost technology.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static Black (Reflective)
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 was first spotted at Kanye West's Yeezy Season 3 and released in September 2016. This 'Black Reflective' colorway touched down in June 2019 and casts the shoe's flexible Primeknit upper in what appears to be a solely black hue. When hit with direct light, the shoe's laces and upper reveal powerful reflective elements that are sewn into the design. The responsive feel of full-length adidas Boost cushioning remains atop a durable rubber sole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Infant)
results.story: First released on February 11, 2017, alongside the identical adult model, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 infant ‘Bred’ combines a black Primeknit upper with red SPLY 350 branding, and a translucent black midsole housing full-length Boost.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (2017/2020)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Bred’ delivers a simplistic colorway of the minimalist lace-up, highlighted by a black Primeknit upper accented with a pronounced center seam and red SPLY-350 branding on the lateral quarter panel. A pull tab at the heel features crimson embroidered detailing for a secondary pop of color. The lightweight build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent black rubber for added durability and support. The original launch date was February 11, 2017, with a restock release on December 5, 2020.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Infant) (Non-Reflective)
results.story: Released in June 2019, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Infant 'Black Non-Reflective' repackages the adult shoe for infant-sized feet. results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Kids) (Non-Reflective)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Black Non-Reflective' shoe casts the coveted sneaker in youth sizing for its June 2019 release. This non-reflective edition reprises many features from 2016's original 350 V2, including a flexible Primeknit upper with a translucent lateral stripe, heel loop and integrated lacing to personalize the fit. For a responsive feel below, adidas' revolutionary Boost cushioning takes position within a translucent TPU shell.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Non-Reflective)
results.story: Conceptualized by musical legend and fashion designer Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is a certified icon for its elusive nature and cult appeal that defines an era. This 'Cloud White Non-Reflective' iteration—issued in September 2019—features a Primeknit bootie constructed with translucent monofilament side stripes and a tonal lacing system. Full-length Boost technology is encased in a tubular rubber sole unit, while the back heel pull is removed from this colorway.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey (Kids)
results.story: Reissued in August 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Kids 'Wave Runner' was first revealed at the Season 5 runway show. This version stays true to the adult original in multicolored mesh counterbalanced by contrasting suede and leather panels. Unique touches include neon-colored laces and perforation on heel. A Boost-cushioned midsole and herringbone rubber outsole give the sneaker its distinctively retro look.

The sneaker rides on an Off-White curved rubber outsole.
